16 Section 1. Section 20-7-1801, MCA, is amended to read:
17 "20-7-1801. Findings -- purpose -- legislative intent. (1) The legislature finds that the ability to read
18 and do mathematics at or above grade level is essential for educational success. The legislature also finds that
19 too many Montana children are not reading proficient in reading or math at the end of 3rd grade.
20 (2) The purposes of this bill are to:
21 (a) provide parents with voluntary early scholastic literacy interventions for their children;
22 (b) increase the number of children who are reading proficient in reading and math at the end of
23 3rd grade and in so doing help those children develop their full educational potential pursuant to Article X,
24 section 1(1), of the Montana constitution; and
25 (c) foster a strong economic return for the state on early scholastic literacy investment through
26 enhancing Montana's skilled workforce and decreasing future reliance on social programs and the criminal
27 justice system.
28 (3) The legislature intends that the board of public education, the office of public instruction, and
