4 Section 3. Section 20-7-1803, MCA, is amended to read:
5 "20-7-1803. Early scholastic literacy targeted interventions. (1) The trustees of a school district
6 may provide eligible children with any one or more of the interventions described in this section. This part may
7 not be construed to limit the duty or authority of trustees to provide educational opportunities described
8 elsewhere in this title.
9 (2) The board of public education shall determine an select at least one evaluation methodology to
10 determine, based on a child's age or grade level, whether the child is above, at, or below a developmental
11 trajectory leading to reading or math proficiency on completion of 3rd grade. The evaluation must be:
12 (a) developmentally appropriate;
13 (b) research-based;
14 (c) cost-effective; and
15 (d) if possible, aligned with formative assessments that inform instruction in the classroom-based
16 program and the jumpstart program.
17 (3) The superintendent of public instruction shall provide school districts with access to and
18 technical support for the evaluation methodology, instrument, or assessment determined selected by the board
19 of public education.
20 (4) A child may not be evaluated for the purposes of this part unless requested by the child's
21 parent or guardian. The trustees may administer the evaluation methodology in April, May, or June to no sooner
22 than 5 months prior to enrolling or upon enrollment of a child who will be 4 years of age or older on or before
23 the following September 10 and who has not yet entered 3rd grade at the time the evaluation methodology is
24 administered. A child who is evaluated to be below trajectory for 3rd-grade reading proficiency or 3rd-grade
25 math proficiency for the child's age or grade level is an eligible child for the subsequent school year.
26 (5) (a) For an eligible child who is 4 years of age or older on or before September 10 of the year in
27 which the child is to participate in the program and who is not entering and who has not completed
28 kindergarten, the trustees may offer a classroom-based program, which may be a half-time or full-time program.
